inn1.comm: that's a jaffa to start off with, phew thatreally kicks up and squares up Gayle just outside off
dropped short! But it didn;t come off the bat, the ball nips away and squares up Gayle, the ball clips his thigh and drops short of first slip
angles it on  the pads and he clips it away and takes off for a quick single, there's a chance at the batsman''s end
fullish outside off and left alone
shapes to play a punchy drive off the backfoot but the ball shoots up and beats the edge
chips down the track and goes for a wild swish through the off side but the ball keeps a bit low and fizzes past the offstump
gets right behind the line and defends with soft hands
leaves it alone outside the offstump
appeal! The ball lands outside leg and keeps a bit low before clipping his pads, Gayle attempts to whip him away
just gets his bat behind the line and defends it away to the off side
grants him width and he helps himself to a wild slash down to third man
he fires it straight and quick, Simmons gets right across his stumps to work it to the on side but he's beaten for pace, the ball catches him plumb in front of middle and off
he stays at the crease and steers it with soft hands to the off side
strays down the leg side and Gayle half heartedly clips it off his legs down to fine leg, the ball rolls away
gets beside the line and steers it to the off side again
once again strays down the leg side and its a fairly quick delivery, Gayle fails to get some wood on it
88.7 mph, raw pace there, he fires it outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
similar speeds, Gayle prods across and hangs his bat out and is completely beaten for pace again
appeal! Did that clip something? Looks like it, another brute of a delivery which kicks up outside off
90.9 mph, that's pace for you, nips away off the seam and beats Sarwan's fish outside the offstump

Broad's in the act again, he hits a good length outside off and gives Sarwan just a hint of width to go for the off-side punch, he obliges but manages a thin outside edge to the keeper, easy decision for umpire Asoka de Silva
88.2 mph, lands it outside off from wide of the crease and the batsman watches it through
pitches it short and angles it towards the left hander, he gets his elbows high and fends it off to the off side
lands it outside off and Chanderpaul safely shoulders arms
angles it on the body and Chanderpaul gets his bat nicely behind the line and taps it to mid-on
rare half volley and Gayle flicks it away from outside off and finds the big spaces at deep midwicket, Strauss gives the chase
clips it softly off his pads to the on side
shoots up alarmingly off a good length, this is terrific bowling, just sneaks past the outside edge
gets behind the line and defends it
88.7 mph, not the most convincing of shots, he shapes to play it straight but gets a leading edge which beats point, the ball gathers pace as it reaches the rope
turns the face of the bat and stylishly clips it away to fine leg
stays back and defends to the off side
attempts a golf swing over the on side but plays too early and the ball clips his thighs and rolls to slip, stifled appeal follows
short and wide outside off, Gayle reaches out and carves it over cover, not quite well-timed, we've seen better from Gayle
chance but the ball drops short! He punches it off the splice of the bat and the ball dips in front of mid-off
take that! Broad overpitches outside off and Gayle thunders it through the line and beats mid-off, nobody moved, I tell you the straight boundary seems awfully short
gets beside the line and slashes it hard to the off side
gets right behind the line and defends on the walk
89 mph, gets across and pushes it inside out to to mid-off
88.2 mph, fullish in length and drifting away from the left-hander, safely shoulders arms
88 mph, angles it on the pads and he clips it to mid-on but there's not enough power on that shot
89.5 mph, keeps it outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
89 mph, gets right across and defends with a dead bat
he connects with that golf shot and the ball keeps going, he stays at the crease, gets on top of the bounce and whams it several rows over wide long-on, looks like they've lost the ball
Gayle stays on the backfoot and waits to bash it away, the ball is wide outside off and he rolls his wrists and thumps it past backward point, it was in the air but safe
strays down the leg side and wide called
84 mph, Gayle waits for it with a high backlift, almost like a baseball batter and thumps it hard but finds backward point this time
comes round the wicket, Chanderpaul tries to club it across the line and gets a thick inside edge onto his pads
lands it outside off and gets it to angle inwards, he safely shoulders arms
bowls the offcutter but he strays a bit too wide outside the offstump
88.7 mph, keeps it a touch wide outside off and Chanders is happy to let it go
88.2 mph, keeps it on the stumps and Gayle gets right behind the line to defend
shapes to slice it through the off side but checks his shot, the ball rolls to backward point
drifts on the pads and Gayle fails to cash in as the ball rolls to square leg
gets his front foot across and thuds it down the pitch
88.5 mph, keeps it outside off and the ball drifts away before reachin the keeper
88.6 mph, gets his front pad across and taps it towards cover
welcome to the crease Mr Swann, a friendly toss up on off and middle and Gayle lofts him through the line and the ball gets lost in the crowd over long-on

timber! Swann isn't afraid to toss it up but this time he puts a lot more pace on the ball, Gayle tries to repeat the loft over long-on but plays all around it and the ball clips the pad slightly and crashes onto the stumps
no turn as it passes the batsman, left alone
slow through the air and he steers it down to gully, Strauss runs across from slip
flatter and quicker, he pushes it through the line to long-on
gets forward and squeezes it past the bat-pad fielder
gets behind the line and defends with a dead bat back to the bowler
86.2 mph, gets a bit across and pats it down the pitch
gets across and pushes it to the off side
bowls the slower one but he drops it short and wide, he reaches out and doesn't hit it too hard, finds the gap between cover and extra cover
gets behind the line and defends softly back to the bowler
85.9 mph, drops it a bit too short and Chanders sizes up for the pull early by swiveling and clipping it off one leg, once again he relies on timing and less on power
flighted on middle and leg, he tucks it to deep square
commits to the front foot and clips it towards square leg
gets well forward and taps it to cover, he tells his partner to wait
gets well forward and defends with a dead bat
skids through and nearly takes the outside edge as he shapes to drive through the covers
falls over as he shapes to sweep and nearly drags his back leg back onto the stumps, the ball rolls to short fine leg
83.5 mph, angles it towards the body and he works it with the angle past square leg, fine leg cuts it off
angles it on the body and he works it to fine leg
reaches out and gets a thick outside edge which beats slip comfortably, third man is fine
88.9 mph, shuffles across his stumps and works it with the angle to Bresnan at fine leg
gets beside the line and defends with a dead bat
80.9 mph, drops it a bit short and he shuffles and tucks it to mid-on
lunges forward and works it against the turn to square leg
gives him the charge and checks his shot as he works it down to short fine leg
flat and quick and he defends
gets a top edge off the sweep and Bravo survives an anxious moment as the ball just clears short fine-leg's reach
flatter and quicker, he defends back to the bowler
flighted on off and pushed to long-on
86 mph, keeps it on middle and he shows the full face of the bat to defend
clipped in the air but safe, the ball is angled on the pads and he clips it in the big gap between mid-on and cover
lands outside off and he safely shoulders arms
loses his radar and drifts on the pads, he just gets a faint edge and works it on its way to fine leg
angles it on the body and he turns the face of the bat and works it to deep square-leg
works it straight to midwicket
dabs it wide of third man and looks for the second but Bravo isn't too keen
the slower ball, he bends forward and plays a very pleasing loft through the line over long-off, nice follow through too, the spectator fumbles the catch
shuffles and works it behind square on the onside
beats him outside the offstump and Prior whips off the bails
chops it down to backward point and it's drinks
gives him width outside off, he hangs his bat out and safely dabs it to third man
not much pace on the ball and it allows Chanders enough time to get across and dab it to third man
swivels and pulls him down to fine leg
lands it outside off, he gets across and taps it to backward point
gets right across his stumps but checks his shot and taps it to the off side
gets across and dabs it down to point
gets across and taps it down to cover
gets his front pad across and defends solidly
shapes to cut but he ends up chopping it down to slip
way too wide outside off and the ball clips Prior's gloves and rolls away, the bowler gets away with a wide call
gets behind the line and defends back to the bowler on the walk
strays on the pads and he works it down to fine leg
gets across to defend but gets a thick edge onto his body
tries to work it to the on side but the ball clips his body and rolls down the pitch, he should have capitalised on that
clips his body and rolls to the on side, Chanders is quickly off the blocks
shuffles across and works it away with the angle down to fine leg
angles it in and Bravo shows the full face of the bat to defend
turns the face of the bat and clips it straight to Bopara at midwicket
gets behind the and defends with soft hands
gives him a bit of width but he softly taps it to cover
good restrictive bowling, Chanders has to settle for a forward defense
gets beside the line and steers it to point, good over so far
lunges forward to defend and he gets a leading edge wide of slip and down to third man
tucks it wide of short midwicket and takes a single to long-on, good over
drops it a bit short and he stays at the crease and swats it down the pitch and wide of mid-on, he used a lot of power on that
stays back and punches him to the off side
has a free swing of the bat and he scoops it over cover
gets across and pulls him wide of square leg
gets behind the line and pushes it to long-on
drifts on the pads and it's a well pitched-up delivery, he lofts him through the line and clears midwicket
full outside off, he leaves it aone
angles across him and beats the outside edge, the extra bounce foxes him and Prior whips off the bails, Chanders' backfoot was intact
good length outside off and he cuts hard to sweeper cover
drifts on the pads and he clips it across the line to deep square-leg
reaches out to a wide delivery and flashes hard but misses
closes the face of the bat and tucks it to short midwicket and decides against the runs
tucks him up for room as he steers it down to point
fullish on the pads and he flicks it away to deep square-leg

and West Indies lose a wicket against the run of play, Chanderpaul goes for an ambitious pull off a delivery which wasn't that short, the top edge swirls in the air for a while and lands safely in Strauss's palms at short third man
chops it to the off side and Bravo tells him to stay back
very well timed, just fractionally wide outside off and he reaches out and chops it so hard on the turf that the ball lobs over backward point comfortably and races away
shuffles and works it away down to the on side
gets behind the line and taps it to cover
extra bounce, the ball holds its line and thuds into Prior's glove
drifts on the body and he helps it along its way to fine leg
clipped away to midwicket, nice sliding save
Collingwood gets a bad bounce at point and that misfield allows a run
Appeal! Prior appeals for the edge and there appeared to be two sounds, no real deviation, perhaps it was bat hitting pad, nevertheless Asoka de Silva wasn't interested
gets forward and defends a full delivery back to the bowler
gets behind the line and defends with soft hands
clips it with the turn to long-on
plenty of revolutions on the ball but off the pitch there's no turn, beats the edge
thrusts forward to defend but the ball beats him again
stays back and punches with the turn to mid-on
stays back and punches it to the offside
extra bounce and Bravo meets the ball in front of Prior's face, gets his elbows high and pulls over midwicket, the ball just drops short of the rope
punches it to mid-off
clips him down to midwicket
gets behind the line and defends with a straight bat
reaches out and taps it to point
gets back and across and taps it softly back to the bowler
gets behind the line and pushes it back to the bowler
pushes a full delivery through the line to long-on and that's his fifty, West Indies really misses him in the Tests
gets back and defends
shifts back, makes room and slices it wide of short third man, the sweeper cover cuts it off
clips it to the on side
gets across and taps it softly to the off side
cramps him for room, he defends back to the bowler
stays back and punches it back to the bowler
angles it wide down the leg side

through the gate! He takes a bit of pace off the ball and gets it to nip back in slightly off the pitch, Bravo leaves a big gap between bat and pad on the drive and the ball crashes on to the off and middle stumps
just manages to defend it away, almost a leading edge
thrusts his pad across and shoulders arms
keeps a bit low and he gets his bat behind the line and defends to cover
short and wide and he slaps it in the air to deep cover, there were cries of 'catch it' but that was far from a chance
clips him through midwicket to get off the mark
flighted on middle and off, he defends to the on side
angles it towards short third man, Anderson does well to slide and cut it off one-handed
lot of flight outside off, he defends with a dead bat
flighted on middle and off, defended again
straighter delivery on the body, he works it away to fine leg
punched right back to the bowler

he lands it on middle and leg and the ball goes through with the line, Ramdin is trapped at the crease and expects it to bounce a lot more but the ball skids through and traps him right in front, easy one for de Silva
skids through and thuds on Prior's glove and the ball rolls to the on side
gets a leading edge but the ball drops in front of point and spins away
pushes it just wide of mid-on and sets off for a quick single
stays back and defends back to the bowler
rocks on the backfoot and defends back to the bowler

it gets worse for the West Indies, Taylor gets forward and pushes it inside out to short mid-off and sets off for a run which was never there, Strauss fires the throw to the keeper and Taylor turns around in desperation and he's a long way out
gets behind and defends
defends to the off side
pushes it softly towards mid-off and sets off for a risky single, the fielder fires a throw to the keeper
gets a nervy inside edge past the stumps, takes a single to short fine leg
kicks up and strikes him on the thigh, stifled appeal for an lbw
full on middle and leg, he pushes it to mid-on and the fielder fumbles as he slides to intercept it one handed
stays behind and defends it to the off side
gets across and pushes it back to the bowler
not much spin, he gets behind and defends
gives it a lot more air and he gets across and clips him high over midwicket
flatter through the air, he gets his bat out and angles it away down to third man, short third man gives the chase, long awaited boundary that
punches it down to long-on
defends on the backfoot
tucks it away to square leg
stays back and punches it hard to cover
confident shot, it is pitched up outside off and  Sammy scoops it wide of mid-on, he knew where the fielder was
full on the offstump and defended back to the bowler
gets well forward and defends
commits to the front foot and blocks it away
87.3 mph, he hangs his bat out and taps it hard to backward point, the fielder slides and cuts it off
stays on the backfoot and pats it back to the bowler, Pollard will have to hit one of these soon
makes room for the upper cut but he fails to ride the bounce
swivels to pull a short delivery and the ball clips his gloves and rolls to short fine leg
stays back and taps it towards cover and sets off
pushes it on the walk to mid-off and puts pressure on the fielder by setting off quickly

I tell you for a few seconds I thought I was looking at an old replay! Collingwood fires it full and on the stumps and Pollard has a wild and blind swing at it, misses it completely and the stumps are disturbed, the drinks break has halted West Indies' ambitions of a recovery
shapes away very late from the left-hander and Benn looks lost, good delivery
stays behind the line and defends softly
tries to take him downtown and the ball swirls in the air towards long-on but dips in front of the fielder
shuffles and works it to the on side
just beats the outside edge, another hopeful prod outside off
shuffles and clips him down to square leg
steps down the track and tries to club him to the on side but he ends up swatting it to cover
Benn goes hell for leather, he shapes to whack it over the on side but mishits it to midwicket, Bopara runs across and falls on the practice pitch as he takes the catch
keeps it short and he taps it back to the bowler
hits the deck hard and the ball clips his body and drops in front of the stumps, thinks of a cheeky single
ends the bouncer, Sammy swishes and misses, the  bat was nowhere near the ball
teases him by angling it across the left hander, he pokes his bat out
gets beside the line and steers it down to point
gets forward to a full delivery and drives quite elegantly wide of extra cover
holds the length back and he pokes his bat out to drive, beats the edge
another beautiful delivery, just shapes across and beats an attempted backfoot drive
full outside off and driven straight to long-off
that's a rarity, Broad pitches it up outside off and a mere defensive push from Rampaul is enough to beat extra cover, the timing was crisp
takes his eye off as he looks to duck a bouncer and the ball hits hm flush on the arm

he expectedly bangs it in short and Rampaul for the second ball in succession takes his eye off and doesn't evade it properly, the ball lobs off his glove and goes to Swann at slip, umpire Hartley raises the finger

inn2.comm: lands it full outside off and he shoulders arms
strays too wide outside the offstump, he safely lets it go
Taylor's struggling with his direction, this one drifts further from the off stump
comes round the wicket and lands it full on the pads, he clips it away wide of midwicket and Pollard does really well to pull it back before the rope, he relays the throw
lazy prod outside the offstump, he gets the ball to nip away
Taylor's nightmare continues, he strays full on the pads and a faint trickle is enough to work it down to fine leg
shapes to drive straight but he gets a thick inside edge past square leg
ends the over on a good note, just gets it to nip away off the seam and foxes Bopara as he reaches out to drive
comes over the wicket, lands it on a good length outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
drifts down the leg side and wide called
Dropped Short and wide and he slaps it hard square of the wicket on the off side, Pollard has it covered to his right but the ball slips out, it travelled quickly though
short and wide again and he chops it to point
loses his line and strays down the leg side, he nudges it off his hips for four to fine leg
reaches out to cut but he mistimes the shot to cover
good finish to the over, nips away off the seam beats his prod outside the off stump
drifts on the body and he clips it down to square leg
gets his front pad across and shoulders arms, he hits a nice line outside the offstump
hits a nice line and length outside off, he sticks his front pad across and shoulders arms
good length outside off, he pushes it towards third man
lands it outside off and the ball holds its line before reaching the keeper
he asks questions outside the offstump, Bopara's bat hits pad as the ball beats him
short of a length outside off, he shoulders arms
gets right behind the line and defends with a straight bat
angles into the right hander, he shuffles and tucks it down to mid-on
we've seen a lot of this today, strays down the leg side and Strauss tries to get some bat in it but the ball clips his pad and beats the keeper
steep bouncer, it sails over Strauss's arched back and the umpire is kind enough not to penalise Rampaul
Bopara's in no hurry, he safely watches it through to the keeper
drops it down to short cover, they decide against the run
gets his elbows high and taps it down to point
shortish delivery and he shoulders arms outside off
gets across and clips it to mid-on
taps it to midwicket and gets off the blocks but decides against the run, that's a maiden
drifts on the pads and he works it away down to wide mid-on
Pollard makes a mess of it, Bopara clips a half volley straigght to square leg and the ball sneaks right between Pollard's legs and runs away,just not West Indies' day
excellent shot, he lands it on the half volley on middle and leg,Bopara shows the full face of the bat and punches it wide of mid-on, the follow through was nice to see
he pokes his bat out and the thick outside edge drops short of first slip
clips it straight to Pollard again and there are loud cheers for the fielder as he picks it up cleanly
angles it on the body from round the wicket, he hops and fends it off to the onside
turns the face of the bat and softly tucks it to short midwicket

three men converge and thankfully someone takes it, short of a length, Strauss tries to nudge it to the on side but gets a thick top edge, the bowler, backward point and Sammy from the slips rush towards it but Sammy hangs on

drops it to the on side and Prior was struggling a bit to make his ground, Bravo charges from square leg, underarms the ball towards the stumps and misses, he collides with Prior and flips to the ground, well he's ok
reaches out to drive and gets a thick inside edge to the stumps
stays on the backfoot and defends towards cover
tempts him with a wide delivery outside off but Prior opts to let it go
turns the face of the bat and clips it towards mid-on and tells his partner to stay back
nips back in sharply, clips his thigh and rolls to the off side
short outside off, he gets his elbows high and upper cuts it over the slips but he finds third man
opens the face of the bat and steers him wide of backward point
shuffles and clips it down to midwicket
drops it a bit short and he opens the face of the bat and steers him down to third man
drops it short and he gets right behind the line and defends
keeps a bit low outside off, he opens the face and glides it wide of second slip
strays on the pads, he gets a half stride forward, rolls his wrists and flicks it wide of midwicket, the ball races away
slower ball, he checks his shot and works it down to square leg
drops it short of a length and he hops and defends it to cover
nice line just outside off, he shows the full face of the bat and defends
makes Prior hop at the crease but he does well to check his shot and fend it wide of second slip
pushes forward and drives to cover

opens the face of the bat and steers it wide of backward point, Prior wanted the second one and charged off and Bopara ended up rushing to the other end, Ramdin fires the ball to the bowler's end but the fielder at the stumps fumbles and that allows a third run
good length outside off, he defends it to the off side
stays on the backfoot and punches it towards the covers
repeats the shot, he's defending well, West Indies have kept things a bit tight, that's the least they can do given the situation
another delivery pushed back to the bowler
short of a length on the offstump, he steers it to cover
hops and clips it to square leg, he tells his partner to stay back
drops it short and wide and Prior expects the bouncer to be called a wide but nope
stands tall and punches him down to mid-off
good length on middle and leg and he whips it away past the big gap between mid-on and midwicket, the ball slows down before the rope, nice shot all the same
the oversteps spoils a good bouncer, the batsman withdraws the hook at the last minute
dishes this one wide outside off but the batsman decides not to play a shot
a misfield and it's Bravo of all people, he gets across to stop a checked drive off the front foot at point but over-runs the ball
tucks it to short mid-on and he sets off initially and realises its not worth the risk
short ball and he sways backwards and plays an upper cut, the ball dips in front of Rampaul at third man
misdirects the slower ball down the legside, Bopara opts out of the shot
hops at the crease and fends it off to point
angles it on the pads from wide of the crease and Bopara just milks it away with a flick of the wrists, there's no midwicket so Benn has to give the chase from mid-on
stays right behind the line and defends back to the bowler
just manages to duck under the bouncer, the ball didn't kick up too much
clips it to the vacant square leg region, big spaces on the on side
fullish in length outside off and he softly pushes it wide of backward point
the bowling change works! Prior is cramped for a bit of room as he tries to run it down to third man, the ball clips the top half of the bat and Gayle takes it on the second attempt at wide slip
fullish in length on middle and leg, he pushes it down to mid-on
gets right behind the line and pushes it to mid-off
fuller in length and he pushes it to mid-off again, nice over from Sammy, he's looked to keep things tight
shuffles and works it down to deep square-leg
keeps it outside off, not much pace on the ball, he defends it softly
tucks it away down to midwicket
gets right behind the line and defends to the off side
the bouncer sails over his helmet after ducking down and de Silva signals the one bouncer for the over
pushes a full delivery down towards mid-on
opens the face of the bat and steers him wide of backward point, third man is square enough to cut it off
gets his bat behind the line and pushes it to cover
finds cover again, Shah cannot break free
the frustration gets to him as he swings and misses, the ball keeps low and fizzes past the offstump
keeps it outside off, he gets behind the line and defends to the off side
loopy bounce outside the offstump and he gets his elbows high and punches it to third man
that will make Shah feel a lot better! Bravo drops it too short and the batsman picks the length early and clubs him over wide midwicket, the ball lands well clear of the fielder at the deep
clips it away for a single
gets across and tucks it wide of square leg
rolls his wrists and clips it off his pads to fine leg
steers it just wide of backward point and takes off for a quick single
gets behind the line and defends to mid-off
taps it back to the bowler, Sammy's keeping things tight
shuffles and works it behind square on the on side
good length outside off and he forces it to the off side
walks down the pitch and across the stumps, he opens the face and deliberately runs it down to third man
angled on the pads and he works it wide of midwicket
gets on one leg and pushes it down to backward point, packed off side field there
short outside off and he glides it down to third man
gets forward and steers it away but backward point's there
that looked like four the minute it left the bat but extra cover was there to cut it off, nice shot off the front foot
slower ball, he stays behind the line and defends
turns the face of the bat and works it to midwicket
gives him width outside off, he reaches out and cuts to sweeper cover
he gets the arm ball and manages to defend it away
drives on the front foot but gets an inside edge onto his boot
full on middle and leg and worked to the on side
prods forward and defends with a dead bat
he pulls a short delivery in front of his face but finds the boundary rider at deep square-leg
slower ball outside off and he dabs it down to third man
the swing beats him, the ball swerves in and lands just outside the line of the offstump, holds its line and hits him in front of the legstump as he tries to flick it, umpire de Silva is convinced
bangs it in short and wide outside off and Collingwood is happy to let that go
just gets it to drift back in, he gets behind the line and defends
swings it in and he softly clips it down to midwicket
opens the face of the bat and steers it with soft hands to point
fires it quick and on the blockhole, he manages to dig it out
grants him width and he reaches out and slaps him down to sweeper cover
gives it a lot of air, he gets his bat down and squeezes it out
turns the face of the bat and tucks it down to square leg
much quicker through the air and the batsman squirts it back to the bowler
rocks on the backfoot and punches him to deep cover
gets to the pitch of the ball and drives just wide of mid-off
angles it on middle and leg, he turns the face of the bat and clips him down to square leg
tries to run the slower ball down to third man but he checks his shot and the ball rolls to the keeper
opens the face and dabs it down to third man
slower ball on the offstump, he defends back to the bowler
drifts down the legside and he clips it off his pads
give it a lot of air and Collingwood's happy to smother the spin
drops it short and he gets enough width to slap it to deep cover
quicker off the pitch, he chops it down to the off side
flighted on middle and off, he clips it to short midwicket
pushed through quicker, he gets an inside edge to the on side
ah Collingwood was waiting for that, Benn was generous with the flight and pace and that allowed the batsman to kneel down and slog him over midwicket
drops it short and he pulls to deep square leg, Rampaul does well to slide and cut it off
stays back and defends to the off side
stays back and pushes it with soft hands to mid-off
drops it short down the leg side, he shapes to hook but the ball just brushes past his body
nice shot! It's a half volley on middle and leg and a mere defensive push is enough to beat mid-on, nice timing
stays behind the line and defends it softly
Collingwood picks the slower delivery well, it's a friendly half volley outside off and Collingwood enjoys a golf swing over long-off
just decides at the last minute to shoulder arms, no turn though
reaches out to a full delivery and finds the gap at cover, long-on sprints across to cut it off
gets well forward and drives back to the bowler
pushes it quicker and flatter, Shah shoulders arms
pushes it full and quick and takes a single to long-off
full outside off and pushed to long-off again
drops it on the offstump and he taps it to the off side
stays behind the line and pushes it to the off side
steers it to the off side and Sammy doesn't time his dive well, quite a comical sight
